{"word":"καταιδέομαι","slug":"καταιδέομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>καταιδέομαι</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a> <el>-αιδέσομαι</el>) (aor1 <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <el>-δέσθην</el>) </el><p/><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a> <i>to feel shame</i> or <i>reverence before</i> another, <i>stand in awe of</i> him, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to be ashamed to do</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/>"}]}